N.Korea Says It Will Hold Talks With U.S. on Soldiers’ Remains

-- B y   W i l l i a m   S i m
-- 
2011-08-19T02:41:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/n-korea-says-it-will-hold-talks-with-u-s-on-soldiers-remains.html
North Korea  said it agreed to hold
talks with the U.S. over the recovery of remains of American
soldiers killed in the 1950-53  Korean War .  North Korea “affirmatively accepted the U.S. proposal for
holding talks,” the state-run Korean Central News Agency said
today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
William Sim in Seoul at 
 wsim2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Panckhurst at 
 ppanckhurst@bloomberg.net  